The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Indian UK plot 

 London, Oct. 12 (Agencies): 

 India-born Dhiren Barot today admitted in a London court 

 today to plotting to blow up financial targets in the US 

 and carry out dirty bomb attacks in britain.

 The 34-year-old London-based Barot alias Abu Musa al-Hindi planned to use a radioactive dirty bomb in one of a series of attacks in Britain, the court was told. He intended to cause injury, fear, terror and chaos, prosecutors said.

 Barot also admitted to plotting to blow up the World Bank and IMF headquarters in Washington, the New York Stock Exchange and the Citigroup building in Manhattan designed to kill as many innocent people as possible.

 Prosecuting lawyer Edmund Lawson said plans had been found by police on a computer after Barot was arrested in August 2004. 




